<br>
Essentially what happened was this...<br>
<br>
A vampire appeared at the entrance to Mistmoore in Lesser Faydark and started to tell PCs of his tale of woe about how him and his 4 companions were set upon in the woods a long time ago by a creature of enormous power who transformed them into vampires.<br>
<br>
About 50 years after their enslavement, their master(who's name remained unknown to them) disappeared, leaveing them as free vampires.<br>
<br>
Of the 4, one went mad, 2 decided to persue Innoruuk as a source of more evil power, and one sought out all the evil knowledge he could find.<br>
<br>
But the vampire we met at MM, Eragru was his name I believe, sought to end his curse.  And Tunare told him that if he put his brethren down he would be free.<br>
<br>
So that was the PCs jobs, to go to 4 different places accross the world and slay these four vampires and return with their heads.  These tasks were completed by 4 different groups of people(as I'm sure was the intent).<br>
<br>
I happened to be in Kithicore when Borshan spawned.  He was a vampire of course, but also a Shadow Knight of Innoruuk.  I sought to join him in his unholy crusade, but Prunezilla(a PC) got a group together and killed him before I could do so.  And that is how I got into this.  After hearing the story, I went to Mistmoore to try and exact revenge for the death of my master's servent on the creature that ordered him slain.<br>
<br>
After a little roleplaying I was disapointed to find I could not attack Eragru.  He was only yellow to me.<br>
<br>
As for the rewards, everyone who brought back a head got an item and money.  Specifically, I know Prunezilla got a Jade Green Broadsword and 10k platinum.<br>
<br>
After he recieved all the heads and gave out all the rewards, Eragru simply vanished.<br>
<br>
However, the question of who made him into a vampire remains unknown.  Mayong was suggested to Eragru, but he seemed to think that was not the case.<br>
<br>
All in all, a rather entertaining event. <p><img src="http://www.geocities.com/dboulais_1999/Thief03.jpg">
